Dear Mr. Smith,
    
    I am writing to apologize for the delay in completing the project. I understand that the deadline was missed, and I take full responsibility for the situation. I would like to explain the reasons for the delay and outline the steps I will take to ensure that this does not happen again in the future.
    
    The main reason for the delay was a lack of communication between myself and the team. I did not keep everyone informed of the progress of the project, and this led to confusion and misunderstandings. I also did not provide clear instructions and expectations, which made it difficult for the team to complete their tasks on time.
    
    To prevent this from happening again, I will make sure to communicate more effectively with the team. I will hold regular meetings to discuss the progress of the project and provide clear instructions and expectations. I will also make sure to keep everyone informed of any changes or updates.
    
    In addition, I will take steps to improve my time management skills. I will create a detailed project plan and stick to it, making sure to allocate enough time for each task. I will also prioritize my tasks and focus on the most important ones first.
    
    I understand that this delay has caused inconvenience and frustration for the team, and I apologize for that. I am committed to making sure that this does not happen again in the future. I will work hard to complete the project on time and to the highest standards.
    
    Thank you for your understanding and support. I look forward to working with you to complete this project successfully.
    
    Sincerely,
    John Doe
